
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `bzcmp` baraye moghayese kardan file-haye boz shode (compressed) ba estefade az bzip2 ba yek file sade estefade mishavad. Agar file-ha farghi nadashte bashand, chizi chap nemishavad.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `-v`  --> 📢 Chap kardan etela'at bishtar dar morede moghayese.
    🔹 `-s`  --> 🤫 Chap nakardan chizi va faghat code voroodi ra bargardan kardan.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ bzcmp file.txt.bz2 file.txt

    🔹 Moghayese file boz shode `file.txt.bz2` ba file sade `file.txt`.

    $ bzcmp -v file1.txt.bz2 file1.txt

    🔹 Moghayese file-ha ba chap kardane etela'at bishtar.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ bzcmp file.txt.bz2 file.txt
    file.txt.bz2 file.txt differ: char 1, line 1

    🔹 Chap kardane inke file-ha ba ham fargh darand.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `bzcmp` command is used to compare bzip2 compressed files with a regular file. If the files are identical, nothing is printed.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `-v`  --> 📢 Print more verbose information about the comparison.
    🔹 `-s`  --> 🤫 Suppress all normal output; return exit codes only.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ bzcmp file.txt.bz2 file.txt

    🔹 Compare the compressed file `file.txt.bz2` with the regular file `file.txt`.

    $ bzcmp -v file1.txt.bz2 file1.txt

    🔹 Compare the files with verbose output.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ bzcmp file.txt.bz2 file.txt
    file.txt.bz2 file.txt differ: char 1, line 1

    🔹 Output indicating that the files differ.
